flow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Observed in this behavior: success depends on the agent/model recognizing a real bug from changed code. Hypothetical elsewhere: transport/wiring reliability is secondary. LLM-DEP: yes, correctness depends on real model output quality and can vary across runs. MOCK-HIDE: stubbed responses would always pass and miss true detection failures. Rejected higher level: Workflow is disqualified because behavior text requires one detection outcome, not a multi-agent or multi-agentic-step chain.","test_description":"Use a real PR fixture with a seeded known bug and run the real model-backed reviewer; assert at least one posted/generated finding correctly points to that defect.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: consistency between two outputs of the run (inline comments set vs summary list). Hypothetical elsewhere: real API delivery issues or model quality are not necessary to validate this invariant. MOCK-MISS: this is cross-module state propagation (comment posting results -> summary composer), not only one local function. INTEGRATION-BRAKE checks: (a) real OS/network/subprocess needed? no; (b) real AI output quality needed? no; (c) multiple agentic steps? no. Rejected higher level: System disqualified because behavior text is about correspondence invariant, testable with in-process fake comment sink.","test_description":"Execute orchestrator with deterministic findings and a fake review-comment sink